At 12:25 PM 4/18/2002 -0700, Glen in Utah wrote:
>Would someone recommend a good anti-seize compound for
>the spark-plug threads.

I use Bostik NEVER-SEEZ(R) for everything, including exhaust nuts.
It contains both aluminum and copper, and is supposedly good
to 1800 deg. F.  I got mine in a brush-top can, from Enco, if I remember
correctly.

